snippet.textDisplay:
Right now, there are people all over the world who are just like you.
They're either lonely, they're missing somebody, they're depressed, they're hurt, they're scarred from the past, they're having personal issues no one knows about, they have secrets you wouldn't believe. 
They wish, they dream and they hope. And right now, they are sitting here reading these words, and I'm writing this for you so you dont feel alone anymore.
Always remember, don't be depressed about the past, don't worry about the future, and just focus on today.
If today's not so great don't worry! Tomorrow's a new chance. If you are reading this, be sure to share this around to make others feel better.
Have a nice day! :)

Sugoi jinsei wo okuttekita. Ikiterunoga fushigina kurai. Tekikara iikagenni shinebato iwaretakedo ichido shindemo soushikide ikikaetta. Watashi niwa tokubetsuna jinseiwo kamisamaga kimetanndana. 
Books no kaitakedo hokanohitono sakuhinni sareteshimatta. Sonouchi kitto iikotogaaru. Name mo tsukawareterushi. Kosekigakariwa sekaide tadahitorino name to shirabetekuretanoni. Tsukauto iuhitogaarawarete cancel shitemo tsukawareta. Darekaga itteta. Onaji name wo tsukatteruhitowa mina shinu to itteta. Watashi dakega nokorurashii. Hontoukana....
Iiya, kitto good future.  Thanks.

snippet.textDisplay:
This is just a story, been keeping it in for a long time, just wanted a medium for me to express it.
I have a good life, good parents, family, and pretty much everything. 
It's not perfect, but it's more than anything I could've asked for.
But despite all that, there's this emptiness in my heart. 
Sometimes I lay in bed staring at my ceiling. Not noticing it had been several hours of doing nothing.
I got sad watching dramas, but I didn't when my friend died long ago.
I'm disturbed by the thought of myself unable to feel sad towards reality but being able to towards fantasy.
My family are all Muslim.
I'm born a Muslim but I think it's just on paper, I'm a bad Muslim.
At night, no matter the weather, I enjoy watching the skies. It felt so comforting to me.
I don't know if this emptiness will go away or not, I really hope so.
People said it'll go away once I felt genuine love.
My parents truly love me, I had girlfriends before that truly loved me and I honestly love them all still.
I let them go to prevent them from sinking with me. There's also someone who said, you'll never let them go if you truly love them.
Maybe they're right, I don't know. 
What I know is, I still can't bring myself to be normal.
Once, I tried to commit suicide because I'm curious of how someone would felt minutes before death.
The only reason I didn't do it was because I thought to myself, "I would hate seeing a dead body while preparing my breakfast",that's why.
Anybody would think I'm an ungrateful person for still nagging.
I don't really care because it's kinda true. Bitching bout life where some people can't even give milk to their babies.
Sometimes, I would sit at a park alone without any devices on me.
I would watch everyone and simulate their personality and life in my head. 
I consider it to be my favorite thing to do.
Meeting a stranger and having conversations to me is one of life's wonder.
There's many things to say but feeling kinda sleepy hearing these sweet lullabies calming down my hurricane of thoughts. 
To anyone that has read this, have a peaceful life. Because I'm still yearning for it, if you had the opportunity, don't take it for granted. Seize it! Don't ever let go.
Because in the end, life is about the connections you made, not the things you profit from.
